# Confluence feedback → Jira tickets

Use when the user asks to triage feedback, create tickets from Confluence, or process the feedback inbox.

## Source page

- **Confluence space:** KAN (Nymphicus)
- **Page title:** `Product Feedback Inbox (Website + Platform)`
- **URL:** https://nymphicusai.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/KAN/pages/2850818/Product+Feedback+Inbox+Website+Platform
- **Cloud:** nymphicusai.atlassian.net

Fetch with Atlassian MCP: `getConfluencePage` or `searchConfluenceUsingCql` → `title = "Product Feedback Inbox (Website + Platform)"`.

## Parse the Backlog table

Columns: ID, Status, Product, Type, Priority, Title, Area, Description, Steps, Expected / Actual, Reporter, Jira.

Process rows where **Status** is `new` or `ready` only. Skip `ticket-created`, `done`, `wont-fix`.

## Create Jira issues (project KAN)

| Type column | Jira issue type | Extra labels |
|-------------|-----------------|--------------|
| bug | Task | `bug` |
| suggestion, improvement | Story | — |
| chore, question | Task | — |

**Always set labels:** product label (`website`, `platform`, or both as two labels), plus type if useful.

**Summary format:** `[website] Title` or `[platform] Title` or `[both] Title`

**Description template:**

```markdown
**Feedback ID:** FB-xxx
**Product:** website | platform
**Priority:** …
**Area:** …
**Reporter:** …

## Description
…

## Steps to reproduce
…

## Expected / Actual
…

**Source:** Product Feedback Inbox (Confluence)
```

## After creating tickets

1. Update the Confluence row: `Status` → `ticket-created`, **Jira** → `KAN-xxx`.
2. Use `updateConfluencePage` with the full updated table body.
3. Report created keys to the user.

## Product scope

- **website** → nymphicus-website repo (marketing site, www.nymphi.ai)
- **platform** → app.nymphi.ai / The_Platform (agent builder, org admin, executions, MCP)
- **both** → create one ticket with both labels; note both surfaces in description

## Do not

- Create duplicate tickets for the same FB-xxx ID
- Change template/example rows unless the user asked to triage them (FB-002 is a template — confirm before ticketing)
